                            "chapter": 1,
                            "name": "Tatian: Fragments 1:48",
                            "text": "11  Tatian, the patriarch of the Encratites, who himself rejected some of Paul's Epistles, believed this especially, that is addressed to Titus, ought to be declared to be the apostle's, thinking little of the assertion of Marcion and others, who agree with him on this point."
                        },
